commitResults.messageBody: Added the greet() and line() methods.
Added echo() method. Edited greet() by removing the "Bye" print statement.
Updated echo() method to store the commands given by user instead of immediately outputting it console. Can now list out all the stored commands when user inputs "list".
Created class Task which contains methods related to each Task. Removed static field commandList from class Duke. Edited echo() method in class Duke to account for commands mark and unmark.
Created 3 new classes Deadline, Todo, and Event. All 3 classes inherit from Task. Now able to add tasks of the 3 classes and updated the list command to factor in the new classes.

Added error handling for invalid inputs, including no input, non-task related inputs, and missing information for various task inputs.
Added bye() function for Duke fike.

Added delete functionality with error handling for missing index.
Moved error handling to echo() function.

commitResults.messageTitle: Updated input and output for runtest.sh
commitResults.messageBody: added input and outputs to test for levels 1-6
Now able to store list data from previous sessions using a text file.
Deadlines and events now accept dates in a format such as yyyy-mm-dd format (e.g., 2019-10-15) and print in a different format such as MMM dd yyyy e.g., (Oct 15 2019).
Added classes Parser, TaskList, and Ui to better implement OOP. Changed the organisation of various functions in the other classes as well.
Added every class to anita package and reorganised import statements.
Added JUnit tests for Todo event and parser

Added javadocs for the following classes:
- Duke
- Parser
- Task
- TaskList
Changed intellij settings to suit coding standards. Applied the changes to code. (eg. switch statements)

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'tmp' commit is needed to fix detached head branch.

commitResults.messageBody:
Add case for "find" in Duke class.

Add findTask method in TaskList class.

Users can now make use of the find command to find tasks containing a certain keyword.

Added check style files and dependencies.

Edited all java files such that it now follows the coding convention.

Added fxml dependencies and files.

Created and modified GUI for Anita chatbot.

Duke, Task, TaskList classes: add assert calls.

Assertion calls can help to identify mistakes made in logic.
Useful to have some simple checks to catch mistakes.

Add assertion calls to check for null objects and range of index.

Done using assert statements to throw assertions when running.

Some methods in the codebase are unnecessarily written as public.

To enhance code maintainability and prevent unintended modification or misuse of internal functionality.
Restricting access to these methods can enforce better encapsulation and reduce the risk of introducing unexpected behaviour during future modifications.

Identified public methods get(int index) in TaskList class and getStatusIcon() in the Task abstract class are being refactored to private access modifiers.

Making these methods private encapsulates their behaviour, limiting their visibility and access to other parts of the codebase.
Add assertion
Make method private
Added getLast() method for future expansions
Added "t", "d", and "e" commands as shortcuts for "todo", "deadline", and "event" respectively.

Added border boxes and a minimum size around the text chat to simulate a live chat.

Remove height restriction on dialogue box to allow all tasks to be shown without being cut off.

Changed font of chat to fix logo.

Increased length of ui.line() to fit the GUI dialogue box.

Removed calls for ui.line() in main file.
Added title for GUI and updated shadowjar.

Fixed a bug where the new status of the marked and unmarked tasks was not saved to the database.

This caused the original status to be lost and replaced with a default "false".

Fixed by changing the representation of saved data in the database.

Also changed the syntax for loading and unloading data.

Added new function Database.changeLine() to allow for the changing of status within the database.
Updated the user guide portion to allow users to learn about various functionalities of the bot.
Added fixes for javadocs comments.
Added more unit testing for allocateTask function.
Formatted README.md to be more user friendly.
Previously database did not check if directory exists.
